"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-paris-2024-olympic-medals-to-be-replaced-after-they-flake-and-rust\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Frank Dalleres  Sports Editor  Red-faced Olympics chiefs have pledged to replace defective medals from the Paris 2024 Games after more than 100 athletes complained that they have begun to flake and rust.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just days after the closing ceremony, disgruntled athletes began sharing pictures of their damaged medals on social media and demanding they be replaced.\", \"from\": 349, \"to\": 502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American skateboarder Nyjah Huston flagged his defective bronze medal within two weeks of receiving it, saying it was \\\"looking rough\\\" and \\\"starting to chip off a little\\\".\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999980081121805, \"rank\": 1.940324666061294e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 526, \"end\": 538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nyjah Huston\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nyjah_Huston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, other medalists have come forward, includingBritish diver Yasmin Harper, who said hers had suffered from \\\"tarnishing\\\" and was \\\"discoloured\\\".\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee said: \\\"Damaged medals will be systematically replaced by the Monnaie de Paris and engraved in an identical way to the originals.\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monnaie de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay in the game with The Turnover: your weekly roundup of sport business news, expert analysis and behind\\u2011the\\u2011scenes stories from City\\u202fAM's sports desk.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1149, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The process to provide any replacements should start in the coming weeks\\u2026 managed by Paris 2024 and Monnaie de Paris, together with the National Olympic Committees of the athletes concerned.\\\"\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Monnaie de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monnaie_de_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9842069865161316, \"rank\": 